    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> @0xanders This looks like a workaround for the EIP's issues with respect to user protection, but the issue itself remains in the EIP... I don't think it's a good candidate for inclusion here.\r\n\r\nFor ENS, there is a Controller role(who can change the data of ENS but can not transfer the NFT), and the owner of the ENS NFT can change the Controller at any time. \r\n\r\nFor Decentraland LAND and ESTATE NFT, there is an Operator role(who can update material to Decentraland but can not transfer the NFT ), the  owner of the LAND or ESTATE NFT can change the Operator at any time.",
